      "attribution": "<div>Board layout and library image by ArnoldSmith86. Released to public domain under CC0.</div><div><br></div>Snake: https://www.svgrepo.com/svg/15737/snake (CC0)",
      "lastUpdate": 1774435056273,
      "skill": "",
      "description": "Create colorful snakes to collect the most cards.",
      "similarImage": "",
      "similarName": "Hisss",
      "similarDesigner": "Brigitte Pokornik",
      "similarAwards": "2002 Japan Boardgame Prize Best Childgame Nominee",
      "ruleText": "<h4>Setup\n</h4><div><ol><li><b>Take seats</b> by clicking them in the top right</li><li><b>Click</b>&nbsp;<i class=\"richtextSymbol material-symbols\">restart_alt</i>&nbsp;to start a new game.</li><li>Put the first card somewhere into the empty space as <b>a start card</b>.</li></ol></div><h4>Turn</h4><div><ol><li><b>Pull a card</b> from the draw pile in the top left.</li><li>Optionally <b>click it to rotate</b> it 180°.</li><li><b>Connect it</b> to an existing snake (matching the color - white is a wildcard) or start a new one.</li><li>If you <b>finish a snake</b> with a head, at least one middle part and a tail, <b>collect its cards</b> into your holder in the top right.</li></ol><div>You may <b>only join</b> existing snakes by <b>using your current card</b>.</div><h4>Game End</h4><div>Whoever has the <b>most cards</b> in their holder, wins. In case of a tie, the player who collected the longest snake wins.</div></div>",
      "helpText": "",
      "usesAIImagery": false,
